OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FRobots to do 39% of home   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ftasks by 2033, say experts 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Within a decade, around 39% of the time
OL,6, spent on housework and caring for loved
OL,7, ones could be automated, experts say.  
OL,9,FResearchers from the UK and Japan asked
OL,10,F65 artificial intelligence (AI) experts
OL,11,Fto predict the amount of automation in 
OL,12,Fcommon household tasks in 10 years.    
OL,14,FExperts predicted grocery shopping was 
OL,15,Flikely to see the most automation,     
OL,16,Fwhile caring for the young or old was  
OL,17,Fthe least likely to be impacted by AI. 
OL,19,FThe research is published in the       
OL,20,Fjournal PLOS ONE.                      
